**Title**: COM - Hardware Community - SAINTCON

**Website**: [saintcon.org](https://saintcon.org/com-hardware-community/)

**Description**: The Hardware Hacking Community (HHC) is a platform for hardware enthusiasts to learn, solder, repair, and experiment with electronic-based hardware. Attendees can work on mini badges and other projects.

**Community Organizer**: Brought to you by Karrots and mav.

**Activities Offered**:
- Soldering projects support (tables, chairs, soldering tools will be provided).
- "How to solder" class available during the conference.
- Suggested bringing personal electronic components/projects for soldering.

**Hours of Operation**:
- Monday: Closed
- Tuesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- Wednesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- Thursday: 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- Friday: 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**Learning Outcomes**:
- Basic Hardware Structure
- Soldering Skills
- PCB Assembly Skills
- Electronic Components Identification
- Advanced hardware diagnostic tools available (Oscilloscopes, Multi-Meters, Bus Pirates).

**Additional Offerings**:
- MiniBadge details to be announced at the community booth.
- Desktop wallpaper available for download.

**Social Media & Resources**:
- Join us on [Discord](https://discord.gg/saintcon).
- MiniBadge Specs on [GitHub](https://github.com/lukejenkins/minibadge).
- Video on how to build a MiniBadge on [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kkLfmo14oiQ).

**Past Events**: 
- SAINTCON 23 (Provo, Utah)
- SAINTCON 22 (Provo, Utah)
- SAINTCON 21 (Provo, Utah)
- SAINTCON 20 (Virtual)
- SAINTCON 19 (Provo, Utah)

**Contact Information**: Support available via provided links (code of conduct, FAQs, registration support, etc.).

